description:
This channel is all about spreading the joy of photography.  Man, that should've been the channel's name!

Anyway, we talk photo gear, styles, philosophies, and techniques.  Videos are mostly weekly. I'm a professional photographer in New Jersey, USA.  I shoot mostly portraits and events.

FAQ:

Are you a full time Youtuber?
No.  I have a photography business in NJ.

What camera do you shoot with?
Whatever gets the job done for the situation.  Canon, Fujifilm, Sony.

What lens do you use?
It doesn't matter....Start seeing the light!  The light is more important than your lens.

Where are you from?
Family is from Puerto Rico.  Was born in Hoboken, NJ.

Family?
Married with two kids

Why do you remind me of Jim Carrey?
I was a huge fan in my 20's and used to make people laugh imitating him.  It stuck. Allllllrighty, then.

description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.‚õ≥Ô∏è

description:
My channel is random photography and video that's compiled on the run and unedited, well, until lately. Some of the best scenes I take credit for are poorly illuminated and blurry, videotaped with a cocked angle as I drive. My interests range from everyday life to bugs, birds and graffiti. I like the hood, airplanes, helicopters and bees.

If there are any interesting areas in Michigan that you would like to have videotaped let me know.


As you can see if you have watched some of my videos one of my favorite places is the south west area of Detroit. The mix between heavy industry, rich history, nature and blight is compelling. The area is loaded with top notch residents that have hung in there through thick and thin. 

If you're aware of any instance where someone is getting a raw deal, please let me know.

I'm always open to suggestions for new content. Thank you for having the same interests as I.

description:
Chris Honoway, a content creator with 20+ years of experience, and a graduate from Eastern Michigan University. Chris studied screenwriting, but quickly realized that video editing was what he was the most proficient in at that time. He made music videos for Detroit legends like Icewear Vezzo, Helluva, Buddie Montana, Jocaine, and Overloaded.

Chris also worked in Los Angeles, & in Europe on music videos and the film "Taryn Barker, Demon Hunter." Since 2017, he's worked with Rock City Music Company, producing events featuring renowned artists like Geddy Lee (RUSH), Alice Cooper, Dee Snider (Twisted Sister), Bruce Kulick (KISS), & Gary Holt (Exodus/Slayer),

After the Covid-19 pandemic, Chris adapted his screenplay "The Redemption in Riverstone Bay," a haunting story about minor league hockey, second chances, and the power of small towns, & family. His ultimate goal is to bring his story to the screen as a television series or motion picture. The paperback and ebook are available now!

As the world's largest production house and tourism content archive of factual 4K UHD video from South Asia, you can make us part of your production plans in India/South Asia. We deliver the widest range of production, gear, location, support services and stock footage.

We can open doors that no one else can - creative, aesthetic, bureaucratic and most importantly - those in the mind! And yes, while some of us have a weakness for wildlife, wilderness and the outdoors, we do produce programming on just about every subject under the sun.

The largest global collection of HD internet and television content on South Asia is now online, as a part of Wilderness Films India's 'A Visual mapping of the Indian Subcontinent' initiative which has taken a team of 100 people some 37 years to put together, and we're doubling up our efforts going forward, in order to archive in HD and 4K every aspect of the South Asian experience! We have 125K clips & films and plan to attain 1 million in 2024.

description:
Welcome,

My name is John Farr. I am an award-winning cinematographer specializing in shooting the highest quality 4K & 8K scenic nature footage. Over the past 20 years, I have traveled to many beautiful places worldwide. The original work I create has been shown in major motion pictures, TV shows, documentaries, and by 4K TV manufacturers. 

I personally suffer from anxiety and I have found nature footage to be an effective tool in relieving stress while promoting relaxation. I put in great effort and personal expense to capture these videos at a specific time & location during optimal conditions. Each video requires over 30 hours of editing, processing, color-enhancing, and adding sound effects/music. 

BETTER HEALTH THERAPY - There are many possible psychological health benefits from watching nature footage including; 
‚Ä¢ Improved Mental Wellness & Peace of Mind
‚Ä¢ Spiritual Healing
‚Ä¢ Anxiety & Stress Relief
‚Ä¢ Rest & Relaxation
‚Ä¢ Improved Meditation & Sleep

Blessings & Peace!
John

To provide quality slow motion videos of baseball pitchers, hitters mechanics and use them as teaching tools when working with students!
Our eyes only see 30 frames per second so when you look at something at full speed, we can only guess what is really going on. When we look at it in slow motion, you are able to see exactly what is going on. Thus, improving teaching quality. I teach hitting and pitching mechanics and use my video library to inspire my students. Please use this library for the same purpose and spread the word!
